CVE-2026-42311: Avoid integer-overflow bypass in tile-extent bounds check.

Adds a pre-validation check on the raw (x0, y0, x1, y1) extents so a
malicious tile cannot bypass the existing `xsize + xoff > size` check
via integer overflow. The new check runs before any addition or
subtraction on the extents, so no overflow can occur.

This patch is structured as pure additions and does not depend on
whether CVE-2026-25990's post-block bounds check is present, so it
applies cleanly to PyPI's pillow 12.1.0 sdist with or without other
backported CVE patches already applied.

Backport of upstream commit 58f9a1d166dcb0c274807d4423522d205b0c35ea
(Pillow PR #9520) for Pillow 12.1.0.

